Alex wrote:
&gt; Hi Stack,
&gt; 
&gt; So are you suggesting using the CrawlController instead of a CrawlJobHandler
&gt; in general?  I understand how it feels a little weird with the state being
&gt; modified with the event queue.  If you could give me a little bit more
&gt; insight on what you are suggesting.
&gt; 
I was thinking there&#39;d be an &#39;atomic&#39; checkpoint that takes care of the 
pause, checkpoint, resume steps -- with handling for interruptions by 
operator, etc. It would live in CrawlController.  Let me try and work on 
this today.

That would leave running a timer that on a period invokes this 
overarching checkpoint.  Could be started by the CrawlController if 
appropriate config. in heritrix.properties (The timer should probably 
live in CC too).

What you think?

St.Ack


&gt; I agree with the logging, quick and dirty, added recently, locally.
&gt; 
&gt; Thanks,
&gt; Alex
&gt; 
&gt;  &gt; On your classes:
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; Looks like you&#39;ve added to the crawlPaused method in your
&gt;  &gt; CrawlJobHandler override a check to see if a request to
&gt;  &gt; checkpoint has
&gt;  &gt; been set and if so, you run checkpointing. Checkpointing runs,
&gt;  &gt; crawlCheckpoint is called in your CJH override and you set
&gt;  &gt; &#39;shouldResume&#39; to true so that when crawlPaused is called again after
&gt;  &gt; checkpointing has completed, you&#39;re override invokes resume
&gt;  &gt; (I like your
&gt;  &gt; use of java.util.Timer).
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; One suggestion I&#39;d make is that changing/managing crawler
&gt;  &gt; state should
&gt;  &gt; be done by the CrawlController rather than out of the state change
&gt;  &gt; methods in CJH (CrawlController is overrideable. See
&gt;  &gt; CrawlJob#setupForCrawlStart where we override CC so we can remove
&gt;  &gt; registered MBeans).
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt;  &gt; Would also suggest using a java.util logger in place of calls to
&gt;  &gt; System.out.err.
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; Calling Heritrix#main is working fine for you?  Any reason you don&#39;t
&gt;  &gt; want to do &#39;new Heritrix()&#39; only?  Did you try it?
&gt; 
